# 2p_meet — host walks RIGHT toward the col-55 wall, jets over, then
# stops on the dummy platform. Client walks LEFT. They should end up
# adjacent and both visible in each other's camera.
#
# Pairs with 2p_meet.client.shot. Both run for 850 ticks. Screenshots
# are taken at the SAME tick numbers from each side so direct visual
# diff is possible (host vs client view of "now").
#
# What to look for in the screenshots:
#   - At touch_t540: are both mechs in the same world position from
#     each player's perspective? Are aim arrows pointing consistently?
#   - Does the client's view of the host's mech match the host's view
#     of itself (within snapshot lag)?

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/meet_host
network host 24051
name HostA

# Walk right toward the wall. Jet to clear it. Land + stop so the
# meet screenshots show both mechs on the same plane (camera follows
# host, so we want host on the ground when client is also on ground).
at 150 press right
at 320 press jet
at 380 release jet
at 380 release right
# Now host is in the air; let it drift down + walk a bit more.
at 440 press right
at 470 release right

at 200 shot match_start
at 320 shot walking
at 400 shot jetting_over_wall
at 520 shot meet_t520
at 580 shot meet_t580
at 700 shot summary
at 750 end

contact_sheet sheet cols 3 cell 320 180
